author: Marc Walker
title: 'I had no idea I was pregnant': Woman, 21, unaware she was carrying a baby boy gives birth in ambulance
text:
Emily Wackett and Matthew Charles with their surprise newborn son (Photo: Ian Burt, Archant) Share Get daily updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
A woman aged 21 who had no idea she was pregnant was stunned to give birth after starting her first shift at a new job. 
Emily Wackett had no morning sickness or baby bump and believed the couple of pounds in weight she had put on were down to Christmas overindulgence. 
But just hours after beginning work at a care home in Welborne, Norfolk, she was having her first child in the back of an ambulance - leaving shocked boyfriend Matthew Charles finding out by phone that he was a dad. 
Emily Wackett, who lives at home with parents Alan and Lea, felt under the weather when she turned up for work on January 30. Emily gave birth to a healthy baby boy whom she had no idea she was carrying (Photo: Ian Burt) Read More Baby joy for Britain's youngest mum whose rapist brother's child was taken away after she gave birth at 12 
The healthy baby boy, who is yet to be named, weighed 7lbs when he was born after Emily was in labour for less than an hour. 
Stunned student Matthew, 20, forked out Â£170 for a cab from Middlesex Univeristy in north west London to the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital on hearing the news. 
It came after Emily's sister's boyfriend Tim Baxter, 29, told Matthew:"I don't want to alarm you mate, but we think Emily is having contractions." Mum Emily with her baby boy and proud grandmother Lea Wackett (Photo: Ian Burt, Archant) 
Emily, from Dereham, Norfolk, said: "I suddenly felt a lot of pain in my stomach - I didn't know what was wrong. 
"I know someone who had appendix problems recently so thought maybe that was it." Read More 
She phoned her family and sister Vicky, who has since found out she is 11 weeks pregnant, dashed to the care home with their mum Lea. 
Once aboard the ambulance, a paramedic confirmed Emily was pregnant. Emily and Matthew are delighted to be parents to the shock arrival (Photo: Ian Burt, Archant) 
Vicky said: "With the ambulance rushing to the hospital, I had to hold up the paramedic while Emily was giving birth . 
"Mum couldn't breathe in the panic and had to be treated in hospital herself." 
Matthew, who has been dating Emily for two years, said: "I was in total shock. 
"My immediate concern was for the health of Emily and the baby. Matthew and Emily pose with their son and the new mum's sister Vicky Wackett (Photo: Ian Burt, Archant) 
"I just wanted to get there as quickly as possible. 
"I spoke to Emily on the phone on the way up and was just so relieved to hear that everything was okay. 
"When I first saw her and my baby in the hospital I didn't know what to say. 
"It was incredibly emotional. 
"We didn't plan this but we are so happy. Mum Emily gives her new baby boy a loving kiss (Photo: Ian Burt, Archant) 
"We thought we might have a child one day, when we're a bit older, but hadn't talked about it seriously." 
Emily added: "Everything hasn't sunk in yet, but we're really happy. 
"Our baby is really beautiful and he's so quiet and well behaved. 
"I've got a lot of support around me and we're adapting really well." Like us on Facebook
